node.text: « elysian » [el - ee - sian] • Greek (adj.) Beautiful or creative, divinely inspired; peaceful and perfect.
« ukiyo » [u - key - yo] • Japanese (n.) Living in the moment, detached from the bothers of life.
« komorebi » [ko - mo - re - be] • Japanese (n.) Sunlight that filters through the leaves of trees.
« acatalepsy » (n.) the impossibility of comprehending the universe; the belief that human knowledge can never have true certainty.

« nefelibata » [ne - fe - le - ba - ta] • Portuguese
(n.) One who lives in the clouds of their own imagination or dreams, or one who does not obey conventions of society, literature or art.

« eunoia » [yoo - noy - uh] • Greek
(n.) a pure and well-balanced mind, a good spirit.

« fika » [fee - ka] • Swedish
(n.) a moment to slow down and appreciate the good things in life.

« hygge » [hue - gah] • Danish
(n.) the ritual of enjoying life's simple pleasures.
Be afraid and do it anyway.

Me ven toda cool y la gilada pero en realidad me estaba re cagando de frío.
Just wait another day, I'll be back before you know.
